# Maven & Gradle ☕

## 📖 What are Build Tools?

A **Build Tool** is software that automates the process of:

* Compiling source code
* Managing dependencies
* Running tests
* Packaging applications
* Deploying applications

In Java, the two most popular build tools are:

* 🔹 Maven
* 🔹 Gradle

---

# 🎯 Why Do We Need Build Tools?

Without Build Tools:

❌ Manually download JAR files

❌ Manually manage dependencies

❌ Compile every file manually

❌ Difficult project management

With Build Tools:

✅ Automatic dependency management

✅ Easy project building

✅ Faster development

✅ Better project structure

---

# 🏗 Build Process

```text
Source Code
      │
      ▼
Compile
      │
      ▼
Run Tests
      │
      ▼
Package (JAR/WAR)
      │
      ▼
Deploy
```

---

# 🚀 What is Maven?

**Apache Maven** is a project management and build automation tool used primarily for Java projects.

It follows the **Convention over Configuration** principle.

---

# ⭐ Features of Maven

* Dependency Management
* Project Build Automation
* Standard Project Structure
* Plugin Support
* Easy Integration
* Test Automation

---

# 📂 Maven Project Structure

```text
MyProject/
│
├── src/
│   ├── main/
│   │   ├── java/
│   │   └── resources/
│   │
│   └── test/
│       ├── java/
│       └── resources/
│
├── target/
├── pom.xml
└── README.md
```

---

# 📄 What is pom.xml?

**POM** stands for **Project Object Model**.

It contains:

* Project Information
* Dependencies
* Plugins
* Build Configuration

Example:

```xml
<project>

    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>com.anup</groupId>

    <artifactId>springboot-app</artifactId>

    <version>1.0.0</version>

</project>
```

---

# 📦 Maven Coordinates

| Element    | Description       |
| ---------- | ----------------- |
| groupId    | Organization Name |
| artifactId | Project Name      |
| version    | Project Version   |

Example:

```text
com.anup
     │
     ▼
springboot-app
     │
     ▼
1.0.0
```

---

# 📚 Maven Dependencies

Dependencies are external libraries required by a project.

Example:

```xml
<dependencies>

    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
    </dependency>

</dependencies>
```

---

# 🔌 Maven Plugins

Plugins perform specific tasks.

Examples:

* Compiler Plugin
* Surefire Plugin
* Jar Plugin
* WAR Plugin

Example:

```xml
<build>

    <plugins>

        <plugin>
            <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
        </plugin>

    </plugins>

</build>
```

---

