# 🚀 What is Gradle?

**Gradle** is a modern build automation tool that combines the best features of Maven and Ant.

It uses **Groovy DSL** or **Kotlin DSL** for configuration.

---

# ⭐ Features of Gradle

* Faster Builds
* Incremental Compilation
* Flexible Configuration
* Better Performance
* Multi-Project Support

---

# 📂 Gradle Project Structure

```text
MyProject/
│
├── src/
├── build.gradle
├── settings.gradle
└── build/
```

---

# 📄 build.gradle Example

```gradle
plugins {
    id 'java'
}

repositories {
    mavenCentral()
}

dependencies {
    implementation 'org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-web'
}
```

---

# ⚙ Gradle Build Lifecycle

```text
Initialization
       │
       ▼
Configuration
       │
       ▼
Execution
```

---

# 💻 Common Gradle Commands

## Build Project

```bash
gradle build
```

---

## Run Tests

```bash
gradle test
```

---

## Clean Project

```bash
gradle clean
```

---

## Run Spring Boot Application

```bash
gradle bootRun
```

---

# 📊 Maven vs Gradle

| Feature               | Maven     | Gradle        |
| --------------------- | --------- | ------------- |
| Configuration         | XML       | Groovy/Kotlin |
| Performance           | Good      | Faster        |
| Learning Curve        | Easy      | Moderate      |
| Dependency Management | Excellent | Excellent     |
| Build Speed           | Slower    | Faster        |
| Flexibility           | Less      | More          |

---

